<title><![CDATA[Cranberry, port and orange compote with Vacherin Mont d'Or]]></title>
<description><![CDATA[Vacherin Mont d'Or is a soft and creamy cheese made with milk from the cows that graze on the summit of Mont d'Or in France. It is then made in CharbonniÃ¨res in Switzerland, so is in fact a Swiss cheese. The sweet and sour contrast of cranberries works beautifully with this amazing cheese. Perfect eaten in front of the fire with a bottle of gutsy red.]]></description>
